==Guest access==
Other players may enter a host's house via the [[House Advertisement]] board if advertised, or by selecting the 'Friend's house' option on the [[Portal (Player-owned house)|entrance portal]] and typing the host's name. 

An update allows players to join other players houses as long as they are on the house owners friends list, and in the same world. Players will be unable to enter if the host's Private setting is off, even if their house is advertised. A player who is teleblocked may still enter via the entrance portal.

Other players can remain in a house if the host leaves; Guests will not be immediately removed. Hosts may remove any player from their house by using the 'Kick' right-click option, however this will not prevent re-entry. Players added to your Ignore list will not be able to enter.

[[Ironman Mode|Ironmen]] may not access another player's house, or vice versa.

==Max houses==
A max house is a house containing the highest level features that are considered useful to the average player. These include: 

*An [[Ornate rejuvenation pool]] for restoring stats
*A [[Gilded altar]] for training [[Prayer]]
*An [[Occult altar]] for switching spellbooks
*An [[armour stand]] for repairing degradable armour
*A [[Lectern]] to create [[teletabs]]
*Teleports from the [[Ornate jewellery box]], [[Portal Nexus]], [[Spirit tree & fairy ring|Spiritual Fairy Tree]], and several [[portal]]s.

'''83''' Construction is currently considered to be the lowest Construction level needed for a max house, as it can be used with a crystal saw and spicy stew boost to build an [[ornate jewellery box]]. '''84''' Construction allows to build a [[crystalline portal nexus]] with both boosts, and 90 Construction allows to plant a [[Spirit tree & fairy ring|Spiritual Fairy Tree]] with spicy stew. 

In World 330, the official House Party world, many players who don't own a max house use other player's houses for the above amenities. 

Players can view whose house is available by viewing the [[house advertisement]] board next to each [[Portal (Player-owned house)|house portal]]. This will list the above information in a menu that the player can select from to pick a house to go to.

Players typically teleport to outside of the house with [[Teleport to house]] tabs and set Teleport Inside turned off in the House Options, as seen in the image below.
